data.title: Great food, lovely view
data.text:
I met my friends Sunday at 11 a.m. for brunch at the Garden Bistro. It is a little difficult to find, but it is well marked with signs once you park your car in the parking lot.

Walk around to the back of the buildings and you will find a very pleasant little restaurant with inside or outside seating. If it's a nice day I highly recommend sitting outside with a beautiful view of the lake.

As others have said, it is a limited brunch menu. But what is served is very delicious and I am sure you can find something there that you like.

Two of us had the chicken salad with a side of coleslaw with a small piece of extremely delicious toasted bread. The servings are very large, I feel, for the price you pay, which was only $8.95. My other friend had lox and bagels and also shared a Belgium waffle. Again , the serving sizes were very abundant.  Our bill was only $41 for the three of us , which I felt was extremely reasonable.

The service was good, we were never rushed at all, and as we had each driven approximately 100 miles to meet up, we wanted to have time for a visit.

If you go to the Garden Bistro, be sure not to miss the gardens that are next to it. Take the time to walk through the lovely Gardens there on the lake or you will truly miss a magnificent setting. There is no charge for the gardens.

I highly recommend the Garden Bistro for brunch.

data.title: Nice Sunday Brunch by the lake
data.text: The brunch menu is limited but very good.  Includes salads, sandwiches and breakfast items at reasonable prices.  Inside seating is cold and stark but it was lovely to sit on the patio by the lake.

data.title: Great little visit
data.text: Stopped by and had a few sides of hummus and a bottle of wine with family.  The staff is always incredibly helpful and kind.  Good wine selection an excellent hummus.  It's hard to beat the view across from Lake mirror.

data.title: Great food, water views.
data.text: Found this small restaurant when driving around Lakeland. The salads were delicious, as was the carrot cake and affordably priced. In cooler weather, the patio would be a nice place to sit with a view of the lake. The gardens nearby are also lovely. Great place for a casual lunch.

data.title: great food
data.text: the place is great for a lunch with great deserts also has a very friendly staff which accommodates your request

data.title: Lovely!
data.text: Had lunch twice there and was not disappointed. The smoked salmon BLT is fabulous! The bacon extended past the edges of the bread and they did not skimp on the smoke salmon portion. My daughter had a cup of lentil soup that had good flavor. A friend had the portobello mushroom burger. She said it was delicious and the sauce it came with was addicting. Their sweetened ice tea was just sweet enough.

data.title: View and gourmet lunch!
data.text: You can enjoy the beautiful view of the lake from a table on the covered terrace, a Stella Artois for $3 and a gourmet lunch.  In addition there is a lovely public garden next door worth a quick stroll.  My lobster roll was so good the first day - great bread, large chunks of lobster meat and wonderful seasoning - I came back and had another special of the day the following lunch.  You will not be disappointed.

data.title: A lovely lunch with a beautiful view
data.text:
Tasty luncheon including a glass of wine . Always picturesque dining on the patio ... . Homemade mushroom
Soup was excellent as was the bistro salad . My favorite for lunch in Lakeland

data.title: I love this place
data.text:
I like dinning on the patio so I can look out on Lake Mirror.
I love their brunch too. It is one on my favorites. Their BLT on Sundays is superb.

data.title: Great Lunch Spot!
data.text: What a delightful surprise to find such an amazing cafe! We were heading to enjoy the Hollis Garden and stumbled upon this great local cafe! Barb & Emily were OUTSTANDING!  Delicious Salmon BLT! Portobello Sandwich! WOW! Relaxing, quaint atmosphere. Beautiful location and view of historic Mirror Lake! We were so happy to have found such a great place to eat. The Homemade Lemon Cake with Raspberry drizzle was Epic! We can't wait to come back and try something different! Great job!

data.title: Quaint Cafe
data.text: Garden Bistro is such a good go to spot when you want consistently good food.  The sandwiches are always made fresh.  Had a butternut squash soup and it was a flavor explosion with just a few ingredients.  Less in this case is more! The side of tabouleh was so good, wanted more and it was sold out!  You could even make it just a dessert destination with the selection that they have, but then you would be sad you didn't get lunch as well.

data.title: Wish I'd had more than a simple salad, but I was dieting, and my companions had more exciting fare.
data.text:
For a small cafe- like restaurant in the Hollis Garden, with beautiful views of the lake and outdoor seating plus air conditioned indoor dining,the Garden Bistro is a winner.
Get a look at their cakes! A Dessert island is too much to ignore, but I managed to stick to a large, fresh salad. Sandwiches and wraps and bigger salads with more in them were available too. Good prices we thought. And the extra treat is the gardens themselves, with roses in bloom when we were there.

data.title: Nice, small restaurant for lunch
data.text: A very relaxing place to eat a very good lunch.  The service was good and the food was very tasty.  The desserts are fantastic with a large selection of great looking cakes.

data.title: A fun little place
data.text: Some interesting menu choices with a something for everyone!  Some of the menu items are made in-house with excellent results (hummus and cole slaw),and there are some imaginative sandwiches and salads to choose from as well.  Sitting outside with a view of the lake and beyond was an added extra to an already pleasant, tasty meal.  We would eat here any time!

data.title: Food Good,  under staffed
data.text: Not a fast service in anyway.  Food was served hot and tasted fine. Prices were what I would pay.  Only down fall is the wait time.   They were running around.  Looked under staffed

data.title: Nice setting -- food ok
data.text:
With its lovely lakeside setting, the Garden Bistro has about the best atmosphere of any restaurant in town, especially when the temperature is moderate and you can sit outside.  You can combine the meal with a pleasant before or after lunch walk around the lake.  Combined with the excellent table service, it all adds up to a very nice experience.

Just don't go expecting the best meal of your life.  The food isn't bad.  It's just ordinary.  The sandwiches are better than what you'd get at Subway, but not by much.  And, I'd recommend you skip dessert altogether.  It's just ok, and it isn't worth the dietary or monetary indulgence.

This, of course, is just one person's opinion,  As you can see from other reviewers, this place usually gets high marks.  Go for the setting, but keep your expectations in line.

data.title: Fine, simple, local place - with a view
data.text:
Sit on the covered patio, adjacent to Hollis Gardens, and look across the lawn and the Lake Mirror Promenade and you have the "classic" Lakeland experience. This locally owned, simple little place sits on the bottom level of the Magnolia Building and is one of the nicest places in town for lunch or Sunday brunch. We were there for brunch today. The special was a LARGE lobster roll with a side of tabbouleh: it was excellent and a steal at $10.50. My other guests had the Smoked Salmon BLT which is a regular menu item and really good - and a little different. My other guest had Baked Eggs Florentine: 2 eggs baked in a dish, covered in spinach, cheese, bits of sausage and tomato. This  dish is good but there are better choices. Now for dessert - today there were 4 different kinds of home-made layer cakes and 3 kinds of home-made pies. When you see the cakes you know they are like Mom used to make: about a foot and not commercial looking at all. Service is friendly and informal. You can eat inside or outside but for brunch most prefer outside. One small quibble: they could use more 4-tops outside and cushions for the metal chairs (I guess that is actually 2 quibbles).
My 3-star rating of the food only reflects that this is a simple lunch place: the food is quite good and do not hesitate to try it.,

data.title: Excellent Restaurant
data.text: We just love this place and the food and service is superb, always have lunch here a couple of times when we are over in Florida.  Looking forward to lunch this coming Sunday.

data.title: Lunch before the Garden stroll
data.text: Fresh Salads, Sandwiches, deserts..... Fair pricing.,,, Great Food overlooking the Lake. Dine inside ( AC ) or on the patio--- Pleasant staff and very Clean.

data.title: Amazing!
data.text: Food is always fresh and delicious. Flavors are creative and the atmosphere is awesome, with a great view of the lake. Love that they serve wines by the glass and the selection is very good.
